==Introduction==
A '''Grid Layout''' renders group of components using the following rules:
* a parent 'grid' component creates a virtual grid of cells (by defining the number of columns, rows grow as needed)
* every child component might be placed in any continuous area of the grid defined by the allocated rows and column
* a component location is defined by the grid line numbers: e.g. 1/3 means between 1 and 3 line of the grid (either row or column)
[[File:Grid Layout Concept.png|600px]]
<br/>
See [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Grid_Layout Grid Layout] for more details.

==Definition==
<pre>
<concept>
  <structure layout="grid" gridColumns="{GRID COLUMNS}">
    <group name="A" layout="table"
                gridColumn="{GRID COLUMN}" gridColumnSpan="{GRID COLUMN SPAN}"
                gridRow="{GRID ROW}"       gridRowSpan="{GRID ROW SPAN}"/>                            <!-- first element of the grid -->
      <property name="Property A.1"/>
      <property name="Property A.1"/>
      <property name="Property A.1"/>
    </group>
    <property name="Property A.2.a" layout="table"
                gridColumn="{GRID COLUMN}" gridColumnSpan="{GRID COLUMN SPAN}"
                gridRow="{GRID ROW}"       gridRowSpan="{GRID ROW SPAN}"/>                            <!-- second element of the grid -->
    <property name="Property A.2.b" layout="table" gridColumn="{GRID COLUMN}" gridRow="{GRID ROW}"/>  <!-- fourth element of the grid -->
    <group name="B" type="table"
                gridColumn="{GRID COLUMN}" gridColumnSpan="{GRID COLUMN SPAN}"
                gridRow="{GRID ROW}"       gridRowSpan="{GRID ROW SPAN}"/>                            <!-- first element of the grid -->
      <property name="Property B.1.a">
      <property name="Property B.1.b">
      <property name="Property B.1.c">
    </group>
  <structure>
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {GRID COLUMNS}
| A number of columns to be displayed in a grid.
|-
! {GRID COLUMN}
| A column number where the particular component should be placed.
|-
! {GRID COLUMN SPAN}
| A number of columns then particular component should be stretched to.
|-
! {GRID ROW}
| A row number where the particular component should be placed.
|-
! {GRID ROW SPAN}
| A number of rows the particular component should be stretched to.
|}


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Enclave">
  <structure layout="grid" gridColumns="4">
    <group name="Details" layout="table" gridColumn="1/2" gridRow="1">
      <property name="Title" mandatory="true"/>
      <property name="Classification"/>
      <property name="Start date"/>
      <property name="End date"/>
    </group>
    <property name="Description" mandatory="true" gridColumn="2/3" gridRow="1"/>
    <reference name="Events"  label="Events" refersFrom="Event" property="Is executed on" gridColumn="1/3" gridRow="2/4"/>
    <group name="Sites" type="sections" gridColumn="3/5" gridRow="1/4">
      <chart name="Sites" label=" " type="pie" concept="Site" groupBy="Is managed by" filter="[[Is part of::${Title}]]" legendLocation="e" height="300"/>
      <reference name="Sites"  label=" " refersFrom="Site" property="Is part of"/>
    </group>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


